<class module="videoDriver" runtimeProfile="rt" qualifiedName="com.tridium.videoDriver.camera.BIVideoCamera" name="BIVideoCamera" packageName="com.tridium.videoDriver.camera" public="true" interface="true" abstract="true" category="interface">
<description>
This interface is used to define a camera device in Niagara AX.&#xa; &#xa; To implement the very basics of a video camera a driver developer&#xa; needs to make some flavor of BComponent, preferrably a BDevice that&#xa; implements BIVideoCamera. Alternatively, to makes things quite easy,&#xa; the driver developer may extend from BDdfSimpleVideoCamera in the devVideoDriver&#xa; module (BDdfSimpleVideoCamera implements BIVideoCamera).&#xa; &#xa; To implement a fully-featured, pan-tilt-zoom video camera, a driver&#xa; developer should choose to implement BIVideoPtzCamera instead of this&#xa; interface. Note that BIVideoPtzCamera extends BIVideoCamera. Optionally,&#xa; to simplify the process, the driver developer may extend from BDdfVideoCamera&#xa; in the devVideoDriver module (BDdfVideoCamera implements BIVideoPtzCamera).
</description>
<tag name="@author">lperkins</tag>
<implements>
<type class="javax.baja.sys.BInterface"/>
</implements>
